The reason people don't read the article: They just want to socialize
text:
Many people here like to think HN is some bastion of intellectual conversation, and it is to some extent, but it's still a social network. Or maybe just a social space, because there isn't much of a network since profiles aren't used much.

Post titles are a jumping off point to socializing, and generally reading the article isn't necessary to converse with strangers on the internet. I won't write more, you probably won't read it :)

Nuclear weapons secrets exposed via flashcard apps article insta-dead?
text:
There's a bellingcat article that's been submitted at least 15 times in the last 3 hours, going Dead each time. It's titled "US Soldiers Expose Nuclear Weapons Secrets Via Flashcard Apps"[0] and seems totally within HN's interest area. Also, other articles from the same site seem to have survived.

Is it a glitch? A new-ish ban? Keyword filtering to avoid getting on a list? Zealous users flagging the links?

[0] https://www.bellingcat.com/news/2021/05/28/us-soldiers-expose-nuclear-weapons-secrets-via-flashcard-apps/

ETA: someone vouched for the most recent posting at the time, https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=27317946 , but it's still strange how we got to 15 dead entries in 3 hours.
